cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the efficiency of autoregressive sequence models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a novel method for constructing a sequence of discrete latent variables, which is related to machine learning and deep neural networks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the task of image captioning, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the lack of parallelism in RNNs, which is a common issue in neural networks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
